SIMPLE: hidebound
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hidebound
<hw>Hide"bound`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having
the skin adhering so closely to the ribs and back as not to be easily
loosened or raised; -- said of an animal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Hort.)</fld> <def>Having the bark so close and
constricting that it impedes the growth; -- said of trees.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Untractable; bigoted; obstinately and blindly or
stupidly conservative.</def> <rj><au>Milton. Carlyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Niggardly; penurious.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Quarles.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hideous</ent>⟦br⟧
